text: The Kakkayam shrub frog (Raorchestes ochlandrae) is a frog. It lives in India. Scientists have seen this frog in one place: Kakkayam in the Western Ghat mountains, about 750 meters above sea level. People have seen this frog about 750 meters above sea level. People saw this frog in forest that had never been cut down and nearby forest that had been cut down and was growing back. People saw them on the ground with the dead leaves or on plants as high as 3 m above the ground. Like other frogs in Raorchestes, this frog hatches out of its egg as a small frog with no free-swimming tadpole stage. ==References== Category:Frogs of Asia
title: Raorchestes kakkayamensis
